page.title: 08Some Hemsworth Schools
page.content: {Archbishop Holgate }was opened in 1926 and at present has one hundred and thirty pupils. It is a church school and is visited by the priest each week. Holgate has no uniform and its emblem is a mitre with three crowns. Three clubs are run for children. It is a primary school { {West End }was opened in 1907 and at present has two hundred and forty pupils. It has a blue uniform with a red squirrel for an emblem. It has eleven clubs for both sexes and has twelve teachers plus head. It is a middle scool. {Grove Lea }was opened in 1968. It is quite religious. There are a hundred and sixty-nine pupils. Grove Lea has no uniform, emblem or motto and it has no clubs. It is a primary school.
